headline.main: REPORTERS PROTEST OWI PRESS ROOM MOVE; Davis Is Told It Is a Menace to 'Open Door Policy'

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Dec. 31 -- Newspaper correspondents covering the War Production Board, War Manpower Commission, Office of Price Administration and other war agencies have formally protested against a transfer of the press room of the Office of War Information from its present headquarters, even though the OWI is taken elsewhere.
abstract: US war agencies correspondents protest proposed OWI news room transfer; Davis says change necessary
